Latest trends 
1. SQL First streaming databases
    Risingwave and Materialise: 
    1. This converts the stream into a materialised view.
    2. Incrementally update the table with the materialised views
2. Kafka Protocol supported systems
    Redpanda: Supports Kafka protocol and JVM free, written in C++
    Wrpastream and AutoMQ: They use disk less Kafka with distributed storage S3 as the backend. Consumer rebalancing and all not needed
3. Key trends shifting
    Streaming Agents: They are interacting with streams and detecting anomalies and fixing data issues where LLM as the main processor
    Apache Iceberg as the Universal Sink: With one click data is landing in Iceberg Tables


